net.sf.jclec.mo.listener

Class MOParetoFrontReporter

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.listener.MOReporter
      • net.sf.jclec.mo.listener.MOParetoFrontReporter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IAlgorithmListener, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC

    public class MOParetoFrontReporter
extends MOReporter
    Reporter for multi-objective algorithms that stores the pareto front in a CSV file. It only generates reports on files.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    Version:
    1.0, 1.0
    Author:
    Aurora Ramirez (AR), Jose Raul Romero (JRR), Sebastian Ventura (SV)

    Knowledge Discovery and Intelligent Systems (KDIS) Research Group: http://www.uco.es/grupos/kdis

    See Also:
    MOReporter, Serialized Form

      • configure

        public void configure(org.apache.commons.configuration.Configuration settings)
        Configurable parameters are:
        • report-title (String):

          Report title (file name). "untitled" by default.

        • report-frequency (int):

          Report frequency. 10 by default.

        • report-on-console (boolean):

          Show report on console. True by default.

        • report-on-file (boolean):

          Save report on file. False by default.

        Specific parameters are:

        • filter-archive (boolean):

          Extract non-dominated solutions from the archive. False by default.

        • command-extract (NonDominatedSolutionsExtractor):

          The command that will be used to extract the non dominated solutions. NonDominatedSolutionsExtractor with ParetoComparator by default.If other class should be used, then the configuration file should contain the following parameter:

          • [@type] (String):

            Name of the class that implements the command.

        report-on-console and report-on-file (inherited from MOReporter) are not considered.

        Specified by:
        configure in interface net.sf.jclec.IConfigure
        Overrides:
        configure in class MOReporter
